  "texts": [
    "On the contrary, for both MCC and AUC, it is clear to observe that random forest and Gradient Boosted Machine perform better than the other three models.",
    "This is also true for balanced accuracy, bookmaker informedness and Cohen's Kappa.",
    "The general pattern is that metrics that are having a close to monotonic relationship with prevalence do a poorer job distinguishing among different models while metrics that are more prevalence-independent do a better job.",
    "We also use statistical tests to detect whether the variance in model evaluation between metrics that are more influenced by prevalence (the three F scores, Jaccard Index, TNR, TPR, and Fowlkes Mallows index) and those that are less are statistically significant.",
    "F-test, Bartlett test and Levene test results all show highly statistically significant p-values (we test the difference in variance for the interaction between metric type and model in Bartlett and Levene tests)."
  ],
